==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bovine
<hw>Bo"vine</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>bovinus</ets>, fr. L. <ets>bos</ets>, <ets>bovis</ets>, ox, cow:
cf. F. <ets>bovine</ets>. See <er>Cow</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the genus
<gen>Bos</gen>; relating to, or resembling, the ox or cow; oxlike;
<as>as, the <ex>bovine</ex> genus; a <ex>bovine</ex>
antelope</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having qualities characteristic of oxen or cows;
sluggish and patient; dull; <as>as, a <ex>bovine</ex>
temperament</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>bovine</qex> gaze of gaping rustics.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Black.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bovril</ent>⟦br⟧
